@page "/guides/how-to-get-out-of-debt"
@using SmartBudget.Components.Pages.Blog
@attribute [AllowAnonymous]
@inherits BlogPostBase

<PageTitle>SmartBudget - How to Get Out of Debt Fast</PageTitle>

<link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/blog.css" />

<div class="blog-post-page">
    <div class="container">
        <!-- Breadcrumb -->
        <div class="breadcrumb-container">
            <nav aria-label="Breadcrumb">
                <ol class="breadcrumb">
                    <li class="breadcrumb-item"><a href="/"><i class="bi bi-house-door"></i> Home</a></li>
                    <li class="breadcrumb-item"><i class="bi bi-chevron-right"></i></li>
                    <li class="breadcrumb-item"><a href="/guides">Guides</a></li>
                    <li class="breadcrumb-item"><i class="bi bi-chevron-right"></i></li>
                    <li class="breadcrumb-item active">How to Get Out of Debt</li>
                </ol>
            </nav>
        </div>

        <article class="blog-post">
            <div class="post-header">
                <span class="post-category-badge">Debt Management</span>
                <h1>How to Get Out of Debt Fast</h1>
                <div class="post-meta">
                    <span><i class="bi bi-person-circle"></i> SmartBudget Team</span>
                    <span><i class="bi bi-calendar3"></i> @CurrentDate</span>
                    <span><i class="bi bi-clock"></i> 14 min read</span>
                    <span><i class="bi bi-file-text"></i> Beginner</span>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="post-body-content">
                <p>Getting out of debt is one of the most important steps to financial freedom. This step-by-step plan will help you become debt-free in @CurrentYear.</p>

                <h2>Why Getting Out of Debt Matters</h2>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Financial freedom:</strong> Stop paying interest and keep your money</li>
                    <li><strong>Peace of mind:</strong> Reduce stress and anxiety about money</li>
                    <li><strong>More opportunities:</strong> Use your income for savings and investments</li>
                    <li><strong>Better credit score:</strong> Improve your financial reputation</li>
                </ul>

                <h2>Step 1: List All Your Debts</h2>
                <p>Write down every debt you have:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Credit card balances</li>
                    <li>Personal loans</li>
                    <li>Student loans</li>
                    <li>Car loans</li>
                    <li>Mortgage</li>
                    <li>Money owed to family and friends</li>
                </ul>

                <div class="table-wrapper">
                    <table>
                        <thead>
                            <tr><th>Debt Type</th><th>Balance (₦)</th><th>Interest Rate</th><th>Min Payment</th></tr>
                        </thead>
                        <tbody>
                            <tr><td>Credit Card</td><td>_____</td><td>_____</td><td>_____</td></tr>
                            <tr><td>Personal Loan</td><td>_____</td><td>_____</td><td>_____</td></tr>
                            <tr><td>Student Loan</td><td>_____</td><td>_____</td><td>_____</td></tr>
                            <tr><td>Car Loan</td><td>_____</td><td>_____</td><td>_____</td></tr>
                            <tr><td>Other</td><td>_____</td><td>_____</td><td>_____</td></tr>
                        </tbody>
                    </table>
                </div>

                <h2>Step 2: Know Your Numbers</h2>
                <p>For each debt, note:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Total balance</li>
                    <li>Interest rate</li>
                    <li>Minimum monthly payment</li>
                    <li>Due date</li>
                </ul>

                <h2>Step 3: Choose a Debt Repayment Strategy</h2>

                <h3>Method 1: Debt Avalanche</h3>
                <p>Pay off debts with the <strong>highest interest rates</strong> first. This saves you the most money in interest.</p>
                <p><strong>Pros:</strong> Saves the most money, mathematically optimal</p>
                <p><strong>Cons:</strong> Can take longer to see progress</p>

                <h3>Method 2: Debt Snowball</h3>
                <p>Pay off the <strong>smallest debt</strong> first, then move to the next. This gives you quick wins and motivation.</p>
                <p><strong>Pros:</strong> Provides quick wins, keeps you motivated</p>
                <p><strong>Cons:</strong> May pay more in interest overall</p>

                <div class="table-wrapper">
                    <table>
                        <thead>
                            <tr><th>Method</th><th>Strategy</th><th>Best For</th></tr>
                        </thead>
                        <tbody>
                            <tr><td>Debt Avalanche</td><td>Highest interest first</td><td>Saving money on interest</td></tr>
                            <tr><td>Debt Snowball</td><td>Smallest balance first</td><td>Staying motivated</td></tr>
                        </tbody>
                    </table>
                </div>

                <h2>Step 4: Create a Budget</h2>
                <p>Allocate as much money as possible to debt repayment. Cut unnecessary expenses and redirect that money to your debts.</p>

                <h3>Ways to Free Up Money</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>Cook at home instead of eating out</li>
                    <li>Cancel unused subscriptions</li>
                    <li>Use public transportation</li>
                    <li>Shop with a list to avoid impulse buys</li>
                    <li>Negotiate bills and utilities</li>
                </ul>

                <h2>Step 5: Increase Your Income</h2>
                <p>Consider these side hustles to accelerate debt repayment:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Freelancing:</strong> Use your skills in writing, design, programming, or consulting</li>
                    <li><strong>Ride-sharing or delivery:</strong> Uber, Bolt, or food delivery services</li>
                    <li><strong>Online tutoring:</strong> Teach subjects you're knowledgeable in</li>
                    <li><strong>Sell items:</strong> Declutter and sell items you don't need</li>
                    <li><strong>Ask for a raise:</strong> Negotiate a salary increase at your current job</li>
                </ul>

                <h2>Step 6: Negotiate with Creditors</h2>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Ask for lower interest rates:</strong> Call your credit card companies and request a rate reduction</li>
                    <li><strong>Request payment plans:</strong> Ask for flexible payment options</li>
                    <li><strong>Consider debt consolidation:</strong> Combine multiple debts into one with a lower interest rate</li>
                    <li><strong>Seek professional help:</strong> Consider credit counseling services</li>
                </ul>

                <h2>Step 7: Stay Motivated</h2>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Track your progress:</strong> Use SmartBudget to see your debt decreasing</li>
                    <li><strong>Celebrate milestones:</strong> Reward yourself when you pay off each debt</li>
                    <li><strong>Visualize a debt-free future:</strong> Imagine the freedom you'll have</li>
                    <li><strong>Join a community:</strong> Find support from others on the same journey</li>
                </ul>

                <h2>Tips for Avoiding Debt in the Future</h2>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Build an emergency fund:</strong> 3-6 months of living expenses</li>
                    <li><strong>Live below your means:</strong> Spend less than you earn</li>
                    <li><strong>Use credit cards responsibly:</strong> Pay the full balance each month</li>
                    <li><strong>Create a realistic budget:</strong> Plan for all expenses</li>
                    <li><strong>Save for big purchases:</strong> Avoid financing unless absolutely necessary</li>
                </ul>

                <h2>Sample Debt Repayment Plan</h2>
                <div class="table-wrapper">
                    <table>
                        <thead>
                            <tr><th>Month</th><th>Debt Paid</th><th>Amount (₦)</th><th>Progress</th></tr>
                        </thead>
                        <tbody>
                            <tr><td>Month 1</td><td>Credit Card</td><td>50,000</td><td>15%</td></tr>
                            <tr><td>Month 2</td><td>Credit Card</td><td>50,000</td><td>30%</td></tr>
                            <tr><td>Month 3</td><td>Credit Card</td><td>50,000</td><td>45%</td></tr>
                            <tr><td>Month 4</td><td>Credit Card</td><td>50,000</td><td>60%</td></tr>
                            <tr><td>Month 5</td><td>Credit Card</td><td>50,000</td><td>75%</td></tr>
                            <tr><td>Month 6</td><td>Credit Card</td><td>50,000</td><td>100% ✅</td></tr>
                        </tbody>
                    </table>
                </div>

                <div class="post-cta">
                    <h3>Take Control of Your Debt</h3>
                    <p>Track your debt repayment progress with SmartBudget.</p>
                    <a href="/Account/Register" class="btn-cta">Get Started Free →</a>
                </div>
            </div>
        </article>
    </div>
</div>


@code {
    protected override async Task OnInitializedAsync()
    {
        PageName = "guide-post";
        await base.OnInitializedAsync();
    }
}